## Embedding Providers in Tests

### Mock provider (fast, no server — use for all unit tests)

The mock produces deterministic fake vectors based on input length. It is
used by `embedding_queue` tests and any test that needs an `EmbeddingProvider`
without a live Lemonade Server.

```rust
use u_forge_ai::embeddings::{EmbeddingModelInfo, EmbeddingProvider, EmbeddingProviderType};

const MOCK_DIMS: usize = 16;

struct MockEmbeddingProvider;

#[async_trait::async_trait]
impl EmbeddingProvider for MockEmbeddingProvider {
    async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> anyhow::Result<Vec<f32>> {
        Ok((0..MOCK_DIMS)
            .map(|i| (text.len() as f32 + i as f32) / 100.0)
            .collect())
    }

    async fn embed_batch(&self, texts: Vec<String>) -> anyhow::Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        let mut out = Vec::with_capacity(texts.len());
        for t in &texts {
            out.push(self.embed(t).await?);
        }
        Ok(out)
    }

    fn dimensions(&self) -> anyhow::Result<usize> { Ok(MOCK_DIMS) }
    fn max_tokens(&self) -> anyhow::Result<usize>  { Ok(512) }

    fn provider_type(&self) -> EmbeddingProviderType {
        EmbeddingProviderType::Lemonade
    }

    fn model_info(&self) -> Option<EmbeddingModelInfo> { None }
}
```

### Lemonade Server (integration tests — skipped when server unreachable)

Use `crate::test_helpers::lemonade_url` — it probes `localhost:8000` via the
`GET /api/v1/health` endpoint first, then falls back to the `LEMONADE_URL`
environment variable. Tests skip silently when neither yields a reachable server:

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_lemonade_embed() {
    let Some(url) = crate::test_helpers::lemonade_url().await else {
        eprintln!("Skipping: no Lemonade Server reachable");
        return;
    };

    let provider = u_forge_ai::embeddings::LemonadeProvider::new(&url, "nomic-embed-text")
        .await
        .expect("Connect to Lemonade");

    let embedding = provider.embed("Test text").await.unwrap();
    assert_eq!(embedding.len(), provider.dimensions().unwrap());
}
```

`lemonade_url()` is defined in `src/test_helpers.rs` (compiled `#[cfg(test)]`
only) and delegates to the production `crate::lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()`.
Resolution order:
1. `http://localhost:8000/api/v1` — probed via `GET /api/v1/health` (2 s timeout)
2. `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1` — same probe, explicit IPv4 loopback
3. `LEMONADE_URL` environment variable — accepted as-is, no liveness check

> **There is no FastEmbed / local fallback.** FastEmbed and ONNX Runtime were
> removed in Phase 1. Do not attempt to reference `FastEmbedProvider`,
> `try_new_local_default`, or `FASTEMBED_CACHE_PATH` — they no longer exist.

